<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-3579] DirectoryTaxonomyWriter should throw a proper exception if it was closed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3579</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;DirTaxoWriter may throw random exceptions (NPE, Already Closed - depend on what API you call) after it has been closed/rollback. We should detect up front that it is already closed, and throw AlreadyClosedException.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3573&quot; title=&quot;TaxonomyReader.refresh() is broken, replace its logic with reopen(), following IR.reopen pattern&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-3573&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Doron pointed out a problem with DTW.rollback &amp;#8211; it should call close() rather than refreshReader. I will fix that as well in this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
